The paper discusses the development of safety critical systems involving robots that interact with humans. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as software engineering (cs.SE) since the paper proposes a method for hazard identification during the development process. The paper also discusses the non-deterministic behavior of the systems, which relates to the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of risk analysis methods, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
